# Example of a simple GSLB setup using DNS\n# Assume a primary site at 192.0.2.1 and a failover site at 192.0.2.2\n# Use a low TTL (e.g., 300 seconds) for the DNS records\n\nprimary_site_dns="example.com. 300 IN A 192.0.2.1"\nfailover_site_dns="example.com. 300 IN A 192.0.2.2"\n\n# Use a GSLB solution to detect failures and redirect traffic\n# This can be done using a commercial GSLB product or a custom solution\n# using monitoring tools and DNS updates